description: Residents in Cuba described the moment a 6.8 magnitude earthquake hit the area. The quake comes after weeks of hurricanes and blackouts that have left many on the island reeling.
title: Residents describe moment 6.8 magnitude earthquake hit Cuba

description: HAVANA — A 6.8 magnitude earthquake shook eastern Cuba on Sunday, after weeks of hurricanes and blackouts that have left many on the island reeling.
title: 6.8 magnitude earthquake shakes Cuba after hurricanes and blackouts

description: A soldier for Yemen’s exiled government opened fire on Saudi troops as they exercised in eastern Yemen, killing two of them and wounding another in a rare insider attack during the kingdom’s nearly decadelong war there, officials said Saturday.
title: Soldier with Yemen’s exiled government opens fire, killing 2 Saudi troops and wounding another

description: Israeli strikes killed dozens of people on Sunday in Lebanon and the northern Gaza Strip, where the military has been waging a major offensive for more than a month that aid groups say has further worsened the humanitarian crisis in the besieged enclave.
title: Israeli strikes kill dozens in Lebanon and isolated northern Gaza, officials say

description: LONDON — King Charles III led Remembrance Day commemorations in London on Sunday as the United Kingdom remembered British and Commonwealth servicemen and women who have lost their lives to conflict.
title: Kate returns to official royal duties with commemoration of war dead

description: Ukraine launched its largest drone attack on the Russian capital city of Moscow since the war began in 2022, injuring one person and forcing three major airports to divert flights, as Russia fired an unprecedented 145 drones against Ukraine.
title: Ukraine launches drone attack on Moscow, shutting down airports

description: In a role reversal of sorts, Australia has been taking a more aggressive stance on climate change, while its neighbor New Zealand is accused of pulling back.
title: As Australia puts more focus on climate change, New Zealand is accused of pulling back

description: Tens of thousands of Spaniards marched in the eastern city of Valencia on Saturday to demand the resignation of the regional president in charge of the emergency response to last week’s catastrophic floods that left more than 200 dead and others missing.
title: Tens of thousands of Spaniards demand the resignation of Valencia leader for bungling flood response

description: Princess Kate made her official return to royal duties today following her cancer diagnosis earlier this year. She joined Prince William and King Charles for the Festival of Remembrance. NBC News' Meghan Fitzgerald reports.
title: Princess Kate makes her first official appearance since cancer diagnosis

description: Qatar says it will pull out of ceasefire talks between Israel and Hamas if they don't get serious about ending the fighting. NBC News' Daniele Hamamdjian reports from Beirut.
title: There's been a major setback in the ceasefire talks between Israel and Hamas
